You need to export your theme, and then pass it into the [ThemeProvider][1] component which you should implement at the root of your application. This will pass it down the React tree and so make your theme available to every child component.

Within each child component where you intend to use the theme, you can then call the theme and its properties directly. For example, if you were trying to style a Button component, you would do so like this:

```
&lt;Button
 type=&quot;submit&quot;
 fullWidth
 variant=&quot;contained&quot;
 color=&quot;primary&quot;
&gt;
  Sign In
&lt;/Button&gt;
```

The &#39;color=&quot;primary&quot;&#39; refers to the primary colour attribute set within your theme, this is then accessible due to the implementation of the ThemeProvider component.


  [1]: https://material-ui.com/styles/api/#themeprovider

