To test if a value is equal to several other values, you should use comparison chaining instead of the `and` operator, which simply performs AND operation on the values as Booleans.

Change:

    if turn in (theBoard[&#39;T-L&#39;] and theBoard[&#39;M-L&#39;] and theBoard[&#39;L-L&#39;]):

to:

    if turn == theBoard[&#39;T-L&#39;] == theBoard[&#39;M-L&#39;] == theBoard[&#39;L-L&#39;]:

And do the same for all the other `if` conditions.

